Package com.wyattbyroade.productionoop

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Item
    The Item interface sets up the consistent set of methods that will be used for any manufactured item, contained by any classes that implement it.
    MultimediaControl
    The MultimediaControl interface sets up the consistent set of methods that will be used to control any player object.
    ScreenSpec
    The ScreenSpec interface sets up methods that must be implemented for all screen objects.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AudioPlayer
    The class AudioPlayer derived from Product and implementing methods from MultimediaControl interface.
    AudioPlayerDriver
    The AudioPlayerDriver class is used to instantiate and test AudioPlayer objects.
    Main
    The Main class serves as the driver for the rest of the classes in the package.
    MoviePlayer
    The class MoviePlayer is used to create objects with screens that implement MultimediaControl methods.
    MoviePlayerDriver
    The class MoviePlayer is used to create objects with screens that implement MultimediaControl methods.
    PlayerDriver
    The class PlayerDriver serves as driver class for AudioPlayer and MoviePlayer classes.
    Product
    The abstract class Product is designed to be inherited by child classes for any manufactured product.
    Screen
    The class Screen is used to create objects to hold technical data about part of a manufactured electronic device.
    ScreenDriver
    The ScreenDriver class is used to instantiate and output string representation of a screen object.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ItemType
    The ItemType is an enum-based type designed to categorize all Product subclasses by four specific descriptions and codes.
    MonitorType
    The enum Monitor type.
